    <fr:title text="Whole-Body Conditioned Egocentric Video Prediction">Whole-Body Conditioned Egocentric Video Prediction</fr:title>
  </fr:frontmatter>
  <fr:mainmatter>
    <html:p>Presentation on PEVA. Related work COSMOS.</html:p>
    <html:p>Observation: you can only completely predict changes caused by your own actions. You cannot necessarily predict changes caused by the world.
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[\text {Prediction} = \text {change via your actions} + \text {change via the world}]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <html:p>Problem formulation: given history frames, actions predict what is going to happen in pixel space.</html:p>
    <html:p>Challenges:</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li>There is a strong contextual dependence for both action and vision. Depending on context, you may hold / see things in a different way.</html:li>
  <html:li>Human actions are harder than global condition. Language vs. high DoF control.</html:li></html:ol>
    <html:p>Auto-Regressive diffusion model. Spatial-attention on image space, causal attention on temporal space.</html:p>
    <html:p>Need architecture, so that actions only interact with <html:strong>next</html:strong> image.</html:p>
    <html:p>Adaptive layer-norm.
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(1 + \Delta  \gamma (c)) \cdot  \mathrm {LN}(x) + \Delta  \beta (c)]]></fr:tex>
Adaptive per-frame layer-norm.
<fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[(1 + \Delta  \gamma (c_t)) \cdot  \mathrm {LN}(x_t) + \Delta  \beta (c_t)]]></fr:tex></html:p>
    <html:p>Using PEVA for control. Other approaches</html:p>
    <html:ol><html:li>Diffusion forcing</html:li>
  <html:li>NWM (CDiT)</html:li></html:ol>
    <html:p>Visual geometrially grounded transformer (VGGT).</html:p>
  </fr:mainmatter>
